<div class='flex-box topic-stream'>
<div class='box-cell stories-anchor padded-cell'>
<hgroup class='page-header' id='topics-header'>
<h2>Topics</h2>
</hgroup>
<div class='page-container' id='topic-header'>
<article class='container-fluid'>
<div class='row-fluid'>
<div class='span12' id='topic-summary'>
<h3 id='topic-title'>Ebola</h3>
</div>
</div>
<div class='row-fluid'>
<div class='span3'>
<figure class='topic-figure'>
<img alt="Screen%20shot%202014-10-15%20at%201.15.36%20pm" src="http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE0LzEwLzE1LzA5L1NjcmVlblNob3QyLjlhNGMxLnBuZwpwCXRodW1iCTE1MHgxNTAjCmUJanBn/59ad41ac/9d9/Screen%20Shot%202014-10-15%20at%201.15.36%20PM.jpg" />
<div id='topic-follow'>

</div>
</figure>
</div>
<div class='span13 topic-article-wrapper'>
<div class='wikipedia_article flow-hack'>
<p>The most recent Ebola outbreak began in West Africa and has since spread to Europe and the United States. There is no vaccine for Ebola yet, and the World Health Organization says we could see up to 10,000 new cases per week by December. See below for Mashable's latest coverage of the Ebola outbreak. 
</p><p>
</p><p><h2>Coverage Highlights</h2>
</p><p><strong><ul><li><a href="http://mashable.com/2014/10/10/ebola-deaths-rising-new-warnings/">Ebola Death Toll Eclipses 4,000 With No Signs of Slowing</a></li>
</p><p><li><a href="http://mashable.com/2014/10/09/ebola-vaccine-test-subject/"</a>I Am an Ebola Vaccine Test Subject</a></li>
</p><p><li><a href="http://mashable.com/2014/08/11/ebola-destroying-liberia/">What Life Is Like in an Ebola-Ravaged Country</a></li></ul></strong></p>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</article>
</div>

