<a class='article-category' data-crackerjax href='#'>World</a>
<h1 class='article-title'>
<a href='http://mashable.com/2015/05/09/liberia-ebola-free/'>
Liberia is now Ebola-free, WHO says cautiously</a>
</h1>
</header>
<footer>
<div class='article-byline'><span class='byline-meta'>Written by</span> <span class='byline-author'>The Associated Press</span></div>
<time class='article-date' datetime='Sat, 09 May 2015 12:56:50 +0000'>
about 1 month ago</time>
</footer>
<p class='article-excerpt'>Liberia is now free of Ebola after going 42 days -- twice the maximum incubation period for the deadly disease -- with no new cases.</p>
</div>
</div></article></div><div class='article-container'><article class='post clearfix short sharable' id='post-554904c7b589e47f77001d80'><div class='article-img-container'>
