s been declared safe so far. However, it won't be taken out of the development stage for mass immunisation until the World Health Organization and other regulators decide it's both safe and effective. The real test will come when it's used in affected countries.\n\nSome experts have said that the fact Ebola cases are falling will make it difficult to establish whether the jab offers any protection.\n\n\"Because case numbers are starting to come down it will become harder and harder to show if the vaccine is having any impact,\u201d Prof Jonathan Ball from Nottingham University said.\n\nGSK's chief executive, Sir Andrew Witty, told the BBC they had \"delayed two other vaccine development programmes to free up the space to do this work.\"\n\nThe World Health Organisation has reported over 8,000 deaths from the virus.\n\nThe latest WHO #Ebola situation report is available here http://t.co/QldaARcg3j pic.twitter.com/UC1rTfDdNl\u2014 WHO (@WHO) January 22, 2015\n\nOther vaccines, from Merck, as well as Zmapp, are also in development.\n\nHave something to add to this story? Share it in the comments."},"shares":{"twitter":914,"facebook":128,"pinterest":1,"google_plus":9,"total":1052},"comments_count":0,"image":"http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE1LzAxLzIzLzIxLzQ1ODM4NTM5Nl9jLjQyMTUxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTk1MHg1MzQjCmUJanBn/3f531667/781/458385396_c.jpg","feature_image":"http://rack.2.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE1LzAxLzIzLzIxLzQ1ODM4NTM5Nl9jLjQyMTUxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTE0Mzh4CmUJanBn/770256b8/781/458385396_c.jpg","responsive_images":[{"image":"http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE1LzAxLzIzLzIxLzQ1ODM4NTM5Nl9jLjQyMTUxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTIwMHgxMTUjCmUJanBn/3fe7e965/781/458385396_c.jpg","query":true,"size":"200x115#"},{"image":"http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE1LzAxLzIzLzIxLzQ1ODM4NTM5Nl9jLjQyMTUxLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTQwMHgyMzAjCmUJanBn/d06dbda7/781/458385396_c.jpg","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"400x230#"}],"short_url":"http://on.mash.to/1BjQhq9","choice":false,"spotlight"